---
// Closing summary of bullet-weight tradeoffs. Three cards joined by → arrows.
// Hard-coded because the narrative ordering (most gas → least gas) is article-specific.
---
<div class="pattern-wrap">
  <div class="pattern-cards">
    <article class="pattern-card amber">
      <div class="pattern-weight">95gr</div>
      <div class="pattern-tag">MOST GAS AT EQUAL PF</div>
      <p>
        Needs the highest velocity → biggest charge → most gas mass and highest gas speed.
        Furthest from atmospheric. Benefits most from fast powder, but also <strong>loses
        most if you use the wrong powder.</strong>
      </p>
    </article>

    <div class="pattern-arrow">→</div>

    <article class="pattern-card cyan">
      <div class="pattern-weight">124gr</div>
      <div class="pattern-tag">MODERATE GAS</div>
      <p>
        Lower velocity → smaller charge → less gas. At equal fast powder,
        produces <strong>less gas momentum than 95gr</strong> at the same PF.
        Practical sweet spot — enough velocity for flat trajectories at PCC
        distances while still keeping gas momentum low.
      </p>
    </article>

    <div class="pattern-arrow">→</div>

    <article class="pattern-card blue">
      <div class="pattern-weight">147gr</div>
      <div class="pattern-tag">LEAST GAS — BUT TRADEOFFS</div>
      <p>
        Lowest velocity → smallest charge → least gas momentum. But 884 fps means
        <strong>more drop, more lead on movers, and longer time-to-target</strong> at
        distance — a real penalty in PCC stages with 50+ yard engagements.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .pattern-wrap {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .pattern-cards {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .pattern-card {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 16px;
    background: var(--bg-card-alt);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--border);
  }
  .pattern-card.amber { border-top-color: var(--accent); }
  .pattern-card.cyan { border-top-color: var(--cyan); }
  .pattern-card.blue { border-top-color: var(--blue); }
  .pattern-weight {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .pattern-card.amber .pattern-weight { color: var(--accent); }
  .pattern-card.cyan .pattern-weight { color: var(--cyan); }
  .pattern-card.blue .pattern-weight { color: var(--blue); }
  .pattern-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .pattern-card p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .pattern-arrow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .pattern-cards { flex-direction: column; }
    .pattern-arrow { display: none; }
  }
</style>
